{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"?(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cacheName","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariableName","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing12VariableNameV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"elementSize","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"numberOfElements","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"symbolKind":"init","extendedModule":"VHDLParsing","title":"init(cacheName:elementSize:numberOfElements:)","roleHeading":"Initializer","modules":[{"relatedModules":["VHDLParsing"],"name":"VHDLMemoryStructures"}],"externalID":"s:11VHDLParsing8VHDLFileV20VHDLMemoryStructuresE9cacheName11elementSize16numberOfElementsACSgAA08VariableF0V_S2itcfc"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures","doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing","doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing\/VHDLFile"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"patch":0,"minor":3},"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Create a cache of elements that may be mapped to underlying BRAM structures.","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing\/VHDLFile\/init(cacheName:elementSize:numberOfElements:)"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/vhdlmemorystructures\/vhdlparsing\/vhdlfile\/init(cachename:elementsize:numberofelements:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"init","kind":"keyword"},{"text":"?(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cacheName","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"name","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariableName","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing12VariableNameV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"elementSize","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"size","kind":"internalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"numberOfElements","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"name","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The name of the cache.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"size","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The size of the elements stored within the cache."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"name":"numberOfElements","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The number of elements to store in the cache."}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This initialiser creates a cache of elements that may be smaller than 32-bits and therefore needs to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be encoded into an appropriate 32-bit aligned memory structure. The interface of the cache hides the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"underlying mapping into BRAM and instead provides addresses based on the specific element rather"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"than the underlying memory address. For example, 3 elements each 4 bits are addresses as element 0, 1,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and 2 respectively rather than sharing address 0 within a 32-bit aligned memory space."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The entity of this cache is defined based on element size and reachable address space based on the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"number of elements. An entity with 12 3-bit elements may look like the example below:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["entity Cache is","    port(","        clk: in std_logic;","        address: in std_logic_vector(3 downto 0);","        data: in std_logic_vector(2 downto 0);","        we: in std_logic;","        ready: in std_logic;","        busy: out std_logic;","        value: out std_logic_vector(2 downto 0);","        value_en: out std_logic;","        lastAddress: out std_logic_vector(3 downto 0)","    );","end Cache;"],"syntax":"VHDL"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Each element within the cache is encoded together with an enable bit that indicates whether the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"element is present or not. This allows the cache to be partially filled and the enable bit to be used"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to determine which elements are within the dangling memory space. Read and write operations are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"supported through a "},{"code":"we","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (write enable) bit that is "},{"code":"high","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when writing and "},{"code":"low","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" when reading. The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"value","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" output describes the current element at the given address and is paired with "},{"code":"value_en","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"indicate whether an element exists at the given address. The "},{"code":"data","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" signal specifies the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"new data to be written to the cache when "},{"code":"we","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is "},{"code":"high","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To perform a write, the write "},{"code":"address","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"data`` is set with the new element and the ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"we"},{"code":"and","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"ready"},{"code":"signals are set","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"high"},{"code":". The write will only be initiated when the ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"busy"},{"code":"signal is","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"low"},{"code":". When a write happens, the ","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"busy"},{"code":"signal will go","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"high"},{"code":"until the write is complete. The","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"lastAddress`"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"signal will contain the address of the last element in the cache."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To perform a read, the address signal is set to the read address, the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"we"},{"type":"text","text":" signal is set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"low"},{"type":"text","text":" and the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ready"},{"type":"text","text":" signal is set "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"high"},{"type":"text","text":". The read will only be performed when the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"busy"},{"type":"text","text":" signal is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"low"},{"type":"text","text":". The"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"read will take exactly 1 clock cycle to finish and will not change the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"busy"},{"type":"text","text":" signal during the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operation. The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value"},{"type":"text","text":" signal will contain the element at the given address and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"value_en"},{"type":"text","text":" signal"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"high"},{"type":"text","text":" if the element is present and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"low"},{"type":"text","text":" if the element is not present."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"During the operation of the cache, any detected errors will cause a permanent ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"busy"},{"text":" signal blocking","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"all further use of the cache.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"warning","name":"Warning","type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Please ensure "},{"code":"elementSize","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is less than or equal to 30 bits as large elements are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"currently not supported and will cause the program to crash."}]}]}]}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://VHDLMemoryStructures/documentation/VHDLMemoryStructures/VHDLParsing/VHDLFile":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"extension"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"VHDLFile","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing8VHDLFileV"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing\/VHDLFile","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Create a generic decoder."}],"url":"\/documentation\/vhdlmemorystructures\/vhdlparsing\/vhdlfile","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"VHDLFile"}],"title":"VHDLFile"},"doc://VHDLMemoryStructures/documentation/VHDLMemoryStructures/VHDLParsing":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/vhdlmemorystructures\/vhdlparsing","role":"collection","title":"VHDLParsing"},"doc://VHDLMemoryStructures/documentation/VHDLMemoryStructures":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/vhdlmemorystructures","role":"collection","title":"VHDLMemoryStructures"},"doc://VHDLMemoryStructures/documentation/VHDLMemoryStructures/VHDLParsing/VHDLFile/init(cacheName:elementSize:numberOfElements:)":{"fragments":[{"text":"init","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"?(","kind":"text"},{"text":"cacheName","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"VariableName","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:11VHDLParsing12VariableNameV"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"elementSize","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":", ","kind":"text"},{"text":"numberOfElements","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"text":")","kind":"text"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/documentation\/VHDLMemoryStructures\/VHDLParsing\/VHDLFile\/init(cacheName:elementSize:numberOfElements:)","url":"\/documentation\/vhdlmemorystructures\/vhdlparsing\/vhdlfile\/init(cachename:elementsize:numberofelements:)","title":"init(cacheName:elementSize:numberOfElements:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Create a cache of elements that may be mapped to underlying BRAM structures.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic"}}}